       "            min_impurity_decrease: float, default=0.0<br><br>A node will be split if this split induces a decrease of the impurity<br>greater than or equal to this value.<br>Values must be in the range `[0.0, inf)`.<br><br>The weighted impurity decrease equation is the following::<br><br>    N_t / N * (impurity - N_t_R / N_t * right_impurity<br>                        - N_t_L / N_t * left_impurity)<br><br>where ``N`` is the total number of samples, ``N_t`` is the number of<br>samples at the current node, ``N_t_L`` is the number of samples in the<br>left child, and ``N_t_R`` is the number of samples in the right child.<br><br>``N``, ``N_t``, ``N_t_R`` and ``N_t_L`` all refer to the weighted sum,<br>if ``sample_weight`` is passed.<br><br>.. versionadded:: 0.19</span>\n",
